Yes, you do!

05:11.761 --> 05:13.560
Big! What's up?!

05:13.562 --> 05:14.962
Hey, Ali!

05:14.964 --> 05:16.263
What's up?

05:16.265 --> 05:17.698
What's up? What's up, girl?

05:17.700 --> 05:19.400
Your dad kno you were here?

05:19.402 --> 05:21.268
Yeah, I'm doing my own music now.

05:21.270 --> 05:23.637
- He's excited.
- Excited?

05:23.639 --> 05:25.205
I'm Star. We sing together.

05:25.207 --> 05:26.740
We're in a group.

05:26.742 --> 05:28.542
- There's three of us.
- My sister's in it,

05:28.544 --> 05:30.044
too, but she's not here right now.

05:30.046 --> 05:33.080
She's at church, praying for our Grammy.

05:33.082 --> 05:35.616
She can sing her ass off, trust me.

05:35.618 --> 05:37.685
Her sister can, too.
We're about to do our first demo.

05:37.687 --> 05:39.119
I want you to produce it.

05:39.121 --> 05:40.821
I would, but I got to
go out of town tomorrow.

05:40.823 --> 05:42.323
I'm going on tour.

05:42.325 --> 05:43.824
Oh, that's perfect.
Tomorrow works for us.

05:43.826 --> 05:45.225
We got a deadline anyway.

05:45.227 --> 05:47.127
- Deadline?
- We're entering

05:47.129 --> 05:49.196
the Atlanta Next Best. We
only have two more days.

05:49.198 --> 05:51.398
Oh, so you just so happened

05:51.400 --> 05:54.401
to bump into me at the club tonight.

05:54.403 --> 05:57.271
Maybe we can work something out.

05:57.273 --> 05:58.739
- All right.
- I think that's a yes. Can I get

05:58.741 --> 05:59.873
- a selfie?
- Hold up. In a minute.

05:59.875 --> 06:01.408
Oh.

06:01.410 --> 06:03.377
That was my personal space.

06:03.379 --> 06:05.212
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- We got this.

06:07.283 --> 06:09.049
Why ain't she calling me back?

06:09.051 --> 06:10.918
She thinks you're mad at her.

06:10.920 --> 06:12.753
Well, now I am.

06:14.523 --> 06:15.923
I'll call the bitch.

06:15.925 --> 06:17.558
She ain't gonna bounce a call on me.

06:17.560 --> 06:20.060
Are you the mother?

06:20.062 --> 06:23.097
Yes, I am.

06:23.099 --> 06:25.099
She was in cardiac arrest, but

06:25.101 --> 06:27.101
we successfully resuscitated her.

06:27.103 --> 06:28.969
Thank you, Jesus.

06:28.971 --> 06:32.206
Any idea of where she
got ahold of those drugs?

06:32.208 --> 06:35.642
No, I have no idea, but I'll find out.

06:35.644 --> 06:37.444
- When can I see her?
- The next

06:37.446 --> 06:39.813
24 hours will be critical,
so we're admitting her

06:39.815 --> 06:42.349
in the hospital for further observation.

06:42.351 --> 06:44.418
The nurse'll let you know
when you can see her.

06:48.858 --> 06:52.126
You ever bring that garbage in
my house again, we are done.

06:55.297 --> 06:57.264
Hi, you.

06:57.266 --> 07:01.101
- Man.
- Man, I figured you was dead or in prison.

07:01.103 --> 07:03.303
Not yet. Hey, congratulations, man.

07:03.305 --> 07:05.572
It looks like business is booming.

07:05.574 --> 07:07.908
Yeah, well, I can't complain.

07:07.910 --> 07:09.376
Like the color green.

07:09.378 --> 07:10.844
Who don't?

07:13.949 --> 07:16.950
Don't come in here
asking me for any money.

07:16.952 --> 07:18.786
- I...
- Hey, man, it's nothing like that.

07:18.788 --> 07:20.254
Check it out.

07:20.256 --> 07:22.089
I got a new act.

07:22.091 --> 07:24.191
A girl group.

07:24.193 --> 07:26.527
A girl...? Oh, this is 1985?

07:26.529 --> 07:30.230
Conny, I'm telling you right now,
man, they're gonna be huge.

07:30.232 --> 07:33.400
For real. I mean, pow.

07:35.504 --> 07:39.573
Look... if it ain't happened
for you yet, man, I...

07:39.575 --> 07:41.408
it ain't gonna happen, baby.

07:41.410 --> 07:43.510
Hey, Conny, check this out.

07:43.512 --> 07:45.779
Who took care of you when
you were a P.A., huh?

07:45.781 --> 07:48.415
So don't act like I never
did you a solid before.

07:48.417 --> 07:50.617
We're on a deadline,
and they need a demo.

07:50.619 --> 07:53.487
And you want what... Free studio time?

07:53.489 --> 07:55.322
Come on, Jahil.

07:55.324 --> 07:57.057
I ain't looking for a handout.

07:57.059 --> 07:59.927
I'm asking for your help.

08:02.498 --> 08:04.164
Who you done robbed, man?

08:09.472 --> 08:11.605
All right.

08:11.607 --> 08:13.073
I got a client

08:13.075 --> 08:14.741
that only works in the daytime.

08:14.766 --> 08:16.844
Your girls can take the
night shift tomorrow night.

08:16.846 --> 08:18.545
I'll take it.

08:20.449 --> 08:23.417
Hey, I like the red.

08:26.322 --> 08:28.622
Your daughter's full legal name?

08:28.624 --> 08:30.057
Simone.

08:31.527 --> 08:32.659
Brown.

08:32.660 --> 08:34.861
Age 16.

08:34.864 --> 08:36.263
Frequent drug use.

08:36.265 --> 08:38.631
Any history of psychiatric problems?

08:38.634 --> 08:40.567
I don't think so, no.

08:40.568 --> 08:43.135
You don't think so.

08:43.138 --> 08:45.973
She's a teenager. They... they all crazy.

08:45.975 --> 08:47.441
Well, we're trying to determine

08:47.443 --> 08:51.111
if this was an overdose
or a suicide attempt.

08:51.113 --> 08:52.846
She has been waking up having nightmares.

08:52.848 --> 08:54.781
Waking up screaming and stuff.

08:54.783 --> 08:57.618
I'll need to make a copy
of your insurance card.

08:57.620 --> 09:00.320
I don't have insurance right now.

09:00.322 --> 09:02.022
The emergency room alone

09:02.024 --> 09:04.725
is going to cost over $5,000.

09:04.727 --> 09:07.361
Obamacare has some
very affordable options

09:07.363 --> 09:09.830
for low-income families.

09:09.832 --> 09:12.199
Who said we were low-income?

09:19.875 --> 09:23.210
Yo, Simone, we just got
Big Boi to produce our demo.

09:23.212 --> 09:25.045
How crazy is that?

09:25.047 --> 09:27.281
Where you at? My mama
been calling you all night.

09:27.283 --> 09:29.049
Huh?

09:29.051 --> 09:31.618
Why do you have my sister's
phone? Where's Simone?

09:34.423 --> 09:36.990
Hello? Please, where's my sister?

09:36.992 --> 09:39.326
- Ma'am, you're gonna have to calm down.
- I need to know where...

09:39.328 --> 09:40.994
- Is she back there?
- Calm down. Lower your voice.

09:40.996 --> 09:43.130
Excuse me. Where is my sister?
Her name is Simone.

09:43.132 --> 09:44.932
She's 16. She swallowed a bunch of pills.

09:44.934 --> 09:47.301
Yes. She is stable now. We have
her admitted to the hospital tonight.

09:47.303 --> 09:48.736
Okay, she's back there?
'Cause I need to go see right now.

09:48.760 --> 09:50.911
One person allowed back
there, and her mother

09:50.913 --> 09:51.949
is there with her right now.

09:51.950 --> 09:54.572
What do you mean "her mother"?
We don't got a mother.

09:57.569 --> 10:03.167
♪ Stay with me, baby ♪

10:03.169 --> 10:07.538
♪ I'm here for you ♪

10:07.540 --> 10:11.509
♪ Through the rain,
through the battles ♪

10:11.511 --> 10:13.945
♪ Whatever ♪

10:13.947 --> 10:18.116
♪ I'll be there, too ♪

10:20.553 --> 10:23.321
♪ 'Cause it ain't time to go ♪

10:23.323 --> 10:26.057
♪ Yeah, this I know ♪

10:27.694 --> 10:31.362
♪ We got much more to do ♪

10:33.399 --> 10:36.534
♪ So come on ♪

10:36.536 --> 10:38.936
♪ Come on back ♪

10:38.938 --> 10:42.273
♪ To me. ♪

10:42.275 --> 10:44.909
Star.

10:48.181 --> 10:50.248
Hi.

10:58.925 --> 11:01.025
I saw Mama.

11:02.896 --> 11:05.396
She was ready for me.

11:06.711 --> 11:08.699
I almost didn't even want to come back.

11:08.701 --> 11:10.568
Then why did you?

11:10.570 --> 11:12.637
For you.

11:12.639 --> 11:15.506
I came back for you.

11:15.508 --> 11:18.109
She told me I had to take care of you.

11:18.111 --> 11:21.913
Our mother was a junkie.

11:21.915 --> 11:23.948
She was a junkie, Simone,

11:23.950 --> 11:25.917
and she died because of it,

11:25.919 --> 11:28.586
and you will, too,
if you keep doing this.

11:28.588 --> 11:30.388
You need to get it together.

11:32.358 --> 11:35.326
I can't lose you like I lost her.

11:35.328 --> 11:37.528
It took me too long to find you.

11:40.282 --> 11:44.017
We can be like those real-life
stories, you know?

11:44.955 --> 11:47.956
The ones that inspire people.

11:49.375 --> 11:52.109
We're gonna be on
Good Morning, America

11:52.111 --> 11:53.945
when we're famous.

11:58.888 --> 12:01.419
Tell me about the contest.

12:01.421 --> 12:03.321
Forget about the contest, Simone.

12:03.323 --> 12:06.023
It's over.

12:06.025 --> 12:08.192
Why? Because of me?

12:08.194 --> 12:10.127
Stop it, Simone.

12:10.129 --> 12:13.331
No. I'm not gonna stop it.
That song's really dope.

12:13.333 --> 12:16.267
You just OD'd, bitch.

12:18.171 --> 12:19.704
I hate hospitals.

12:19.706 --> 12:20.807
Put it back in.

12:20.832 --> 12:22.206
You need to stop it.

12:22.208 --> 12:23.541
- No.
- You can't leave.

12:23.543 --> 12:26.077
Simone, stop.

12:26.079 --> 12:28.179
What if they figure out who I am?

12:28.181 --> 12:30.348
What if they figure out what we did?

12:30.350 --> 12:31.949
You really don't think

12:31.951 --> 12:34.585
nobody's gonna come up
in here looking for us?

12:43.162 --> 12:46.230
How long you been sitting here?

12:46.232 --> 12:48.866
A little while.

12:53.339 --> 12:54.839
How is Simone?

12:54.841 --> 12:58.075
Simone is good.

12:58.077 --> 13:01.846
So why you look so sad, baby?

13:01.848 --> 13:04.382
I've been thinking about Matthew 13.

13:04.384 --> 13:06.684
These girls, Bobby.

13:06.686 --> 13:09.153
These girls ain't got no roots.

13:09.155 --> 13:11.822
They ain't got no religion.

13:11.824 --> 13:14.158
I can't go back and undo all that.

13:18.965 --> 13:22.166
Now, look at us.

13:22.168 --> 13:24.902
We didn't have no roots either.

13:24.904 --> 13:26.938
Somehow...

13:26.940 --> 13:29.206
we found our way.

13:29.208 --> 13:32.109
Simone is one thing,

13:32.111 --> 13:34.378
but Star, I don't know.

13:34.380 --> 13:37.915
Yeah, but they just got here.

13:37.917 --> 13:40.751
Go easy, give 'em a minute.

13:42.088 --> 13:43.387
Yeah.

13:43.389 --> 13:47.425
Well, I should get back to the hospital.

14:03.776 --> 14:05.209
Damn, I hope she forgive me.

14:05.211 --> 14:06.477
Carlotta?

14:06.479 --> 14:08.412
Y'all are ride or die.

14:08.414 --> 14:11.015
You know that little
crazy-eyed girl stole my candy.

14:11.017 --> 14:14.251
- Hello?
- But she gonna be all right.

14:14.253 --> 14:16.587
I'm looking for Star.

14:16.589 --> 14:19.590
Oh, my God, bitch,
there go Hunter Morgan.

14:20.793 --> 14:23.094
Come here.

14:23.096 --> 14:25.463
If y'all don't get into it:

14:25.465 --> 14:27.164
35 touchdowns,

14:27.166 --> 14:28.699
68% completion rate.

14:28.701 --> 14:30.568
It's over for you. You turning it.

14:30.570 --> 14:33.070
And since when you
started watching football?

14:33.072 --> 14:36.273
Since his fine ass became quarterback.

14:37.844 --> 14:40.444
Please don't tell me
you're messing with Star.

14:40.446 --> 14:42.947
- Not yet.
- Ugh.

14:42.949 --> 14:45.016
Girl won't return my phone calls.

14:45.018 --> 14:47.018
Let me tell you something.

14:47.020 --> 14:50.287
Star way too complicated
for a man like you.

14:50.289 --> 14:51.889
I see you with a more agreeable

14:51.891 --> 14:54.725
Asian-type girl.

14:54.727 --> 14:56.360
Star ain't here.

14:56.362 --> 14:58.362
They at the hospital with her sister.

14:58.364 --> 14:59.697
Which hospital?

14:59.699 --> 15:01.532
Midtown General.

15:01.534 --> 15:03.534
Okay, thank you.

15:03.536 --> 15:05.856
Simone's ready to go.

15:06.739 --> 15:08.139
Who are you?

15:08.141 --> 15:10.041
I'm Dr. Klein, the on-call psychiatrist.

15:10.043 --> 15:11.876
You're a shrink?

15:11.878 --> 15:13.677
She doesn't need a shrink.

15:13.679 --> 15:15.379
She's a pothead, end of story.

15:15.381 --> 15:16.914
It's, uh, it's more than pot.

15:16.916 --> 15:18.849
We think this may have
been a suicide attempt.

15:18.851 --> 15:20.084
But it wasn't.

15:20.086 --> 15:21.552
She feels great.

15:21.554 --> 15:23.954
She hates it here and she'd
like to leave, cool?

15:23.956 --> 15:25.356
Just to be on the safe side,

15:25.358 --> 15:27.158
I'm ordering a 72-hour psych hold.

15:27.160 --> 15:30.061
A psych hold?

15:30.063 --> 15:32.363
Could you give us a moment, please?

15:32.365 --> 15:35.833
Thank you.

15:35.835 --> 15:38.702
What did you tell them?
Because let me remind you,

15:38.704 --> 15:41.205
you are not our mother,
you barely know us.

15:41.207 --> 15:43.707
Well, I'm the closest thing
she has to a mother right now.

15:43.709 --> 15:45.443
I'm trying to do the best for her.

15:45.445 --> 15:48.946
Since when?

15:48.948 --> 15:51.115
You gave us up.

15:51.117 --> 15:53.784
They used us for free government checks,

15:53.786 --> 15:56.921
free babysitting, free sex.

15:56.923 --> 15:59.156
That man is a doctor.

15:59.158 --> 16:01.559
Do you know what's gonna happen
if he finds out she's a minor

16:01.561 --> 16:02.960
and I'm not her legal guardian?

16:02.962 --> 16:06.764
I'm tired of your speeches.

16:06.766 --> 16:10.000
You were our mother's best friend.

16:10.002 --> 16:13.170
You should have been there for us then.

16:16.075 --> 16:18.709
Star.

